## Design Review Checklist
1. [ ] Does it use SF Pro with proper weights?
2. [ ] Are stroke widths consistent (1.5px)?
3. [ ] Is the 8pt grid followed?
4. [ ] Are primary actions reachable via keyboard?
5. [ ] Does it support both Light and Dark mode gracefully?
6. [ ] Is there enough white space to prevent cognitive load?
7. [ ] Are icons optically aligned with text?
8. [ ] Is the accent color used sparingly?
9. [ ] Do hover states provide immediate feedback?
10. [ ] Is the microcopy concise and verb-led?
11. [ ] Are hit targets large enough for easy clicking?
12. [ ] Does it feel like a native macOS app?
